## Prerequisites

- AWS account with IAM user and access keys
- AWS CLI configured (`aws configure`)
- Terraform installed (v1.0+ recommended)
- Existing AWS key pair (e.g., `Jagadish_Instance`)
- VS Code + Git Bash (optional but recommended)

---

## How to Deploy

### 1. Initialize Terraform
terraform init
#### 2.Validate configuratio
terraform validate
#### 3.Preview the infrastructure
terraform plan -var="key_name=Jagadish_Instance"

##### 4.Apply and launch EC2 instances
terraform apply -var="key_name=Jagadish_Instance" -auto-approve


#### Destroy Infrastructure #####
To avoid charges, destroy everything when done:
terraform destroy -var="key_name=Jagadish_Instance" -auto-approve


###### Free‑Tier Safety Notes
This project avoids all non‑free‑tier components:
- No NAT Gateway (expensive)
- No Load Balancer
- No Elastic IPs
- No RDS or EFS
- No CloudWatch detailed monitoring
- EC2 instances limited to t2.micro
- EBS volumes limited to 8GB each (free tier allows 30GB total)
Running two EC2 instances 24/7 may exceed the monthly 750 free hours, so destroy or stop them when not needed.
